e, decision’ (also, ‘the gods’) + <i>valdr</i> ‘ruler’). This name was regularly used in the Middle Ages in northern England and Scotland, where Scandinavian influence was strong. It is now widespread throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Friedrich von Formbach was born about 1024, his father, Thiemo I. von Formbach, was 46 and his mother, Gräfin von Braunschweig, was 22. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Gertrud von Haldensleben. He died in 1059, in Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Passau, Bavaria, Germany, at the age of 36, and was buried in Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Passau, Bavaria, Germany."},"et":{"Abt 1024–1059":"umbes 1024–1059","1018–1040":"1018–1040","1024–1059":"1024–1059","1025–1116":"1025–1116","1050–1090":"1050–1090","1050–1144":"1050–1144","1052–Female":"1052–Surnud","0980–1049":"0980–1049","1004–Female":"1004–Surnud","1090":"1090","ABT 1059":"umbes 1059","1052":"1052","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","um 1050":"umbes 1050","1018":"1018","1116":"1116","1049":"1049","1059":"1059","1004":"1004","Abt 1024":"umbes 1024","1025":"1025","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1144":"1144","19 MAR 1049":"19. märts 1049","Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Landkreis Passau, Bayern, Deutschland":"Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Landkreis Passau, Bayern, Saksamaa","Schweinachgau, Germany":"Saksamaa","Elsaß, Frankreich":"Alsace, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1024–1059":"noin 1024–1059","1018–1040":"1018–1040","1024–1059":"1024–1059","1025–1116":"1025–1116","1050–1090":"1050–1090","1050–1144":"1050–1144","1052–Female":"1052–Kuollut","0980–1049":"0980–1049","1004–Female":"1004–Kuollut","1090":"1090","ABT 1059":"noin 1059","1052":"1052","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","um 1050":"noin 1050","1018":"1018","1116":"1116","1049":"1049","1059":"1059","1004":"1004","Abt 1024":"noin 1024","1025":"1025","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1144":"1144","19 MAR 1049":"19. maaliskuuta 1049","Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Landkreis Passau, Bayern, Deutschland":"Vornbach, Neuhaus am Inn, Landkreis Pass